												<p>I made these brownies a few days ago and they turned out delicious.  I&#8217;m spending my Christmas vacation at a high elevation (5000 + feet) and the only change I made to the reciepe was increasing the oven temp to 350 degrees and they came out perfectly.  This was my first time baking in high altitudes so I was pleasantly surprised with the outcome.  They have become a little denser a day or two after compared to when they came straight out of the oven, but I think that makes the depth of their flavor so much better.  Thanks for sharing!</p>
